<TITLE> Uttara Motors MD sues Huda for extortion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 5 (bdnews24.com)  A businessman Thursday filed an extortion case against former communications minister Barrister Nazmul Huda, police said. Uttara Motors managing director Matiur Rahman filed the case with Dhanmondi Police Station for extorting Tk 1 crore from him. Dhanmondi police chief Monwar Hossain confirmed the case. According to case details, Huda demanded the sum from Matiur and threatened to scrap the registration of his business firm if he did not comply with the demand. Huda allegedly threatened to kill him and the appellant paid him the money in three installments, the case says. Monwar Hossain told bdnews24.com that the police had opened an investigation into the case. Sub-inspector Amirul Islam has been made investigation officer. Joint forces arrested Huda on Feb 4 at his Dhanmondi home. A few hours before the case filed, Huda and his wife Sigma Huda were charged in a bribery case in a special judge court in the Jatiya Sangsad premises. Sigma was sent to jail. bdnews
